  <num>2-421</num>
  <heading>Right to present claim.</heading>
  <text>Any person unjustly convicted of and subsequently imprisoned for a criminal offense contained in the District of Columbia Official Code may present a claim for damages against the District of Columbia.</text>
  <annotations>
